<p>U.S. officials said the military struck an alleged drug-carrying vessel on Friday, killing three people, an action Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth disclosed on Sunday [cbsnews.com#1][firstpost.com#1][japantoday.com#1]. President Trump, escalating a dispute with Bogotá, said the United States will halt financial aid to Colombia and impose tariffs on its imports because, he argues, President Gustavo Petro is not stopping drug production [npr.org#1][apnews.com#1][ft.com#1]. Colombia rejected the accusations, and Petro earlier accused the United States of “murder” over a prior strike that killed a Colombian fisherman [nytimes.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. Senator Lindsey Graham said he spoke with the President and that tariff rates would be announced Monday, a significant move for a country that still counts the U.S. as its main trading partner [elpais.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/9WPeqSdkCQ57lojqjoewX1JT2RDDs3MGtlBZ3w8-gz4ctxlwIfFf8lgX1K5eN71EMuPYdmq9slLpe0jPlMWKkv9U9j6iwDAfJCQy49M66hPm' alt='Composite images of U.S. President Donald Trump and Colombian President Gustavo Petro.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Trade exposure: Colombia remains one of the few Latin American countries for which the United States is still the main trading partner, increasing its vulnerability to U.S. tariff decisions [elpais.com#1].</li><li>Colombia response: Bogotá condemned the President’s description of Petro as an “illegal drug leader” and rejected the allegations against its government [france24.com#1][straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Regional backdrop: U.S. warships have operated in the Caribbean off Venezuela since August, amid concerns the campaign could pressure Nicolás Maduro’s government [dawn.com#1][france24.com#1].</li><li>Operation location: The Pentagon said the latest strike targeted a vessel in international waters rather than in Colombia’s territorial seas [theguardian.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Three terrorists were killed - Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: He said the U.S. will halt assistance and impose tariffs because Petro “does nothing to stop” drug production. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/20/nx-s1-5579661/trump-tariffs-aid-colombia-amid-clash-drugs-petro'>NPR</a>)</li><li>Colombian government: It condemned the accusation that Petro is an “illegal drug leader” and rejected the U.S. claims. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/us-says-it-hit-colombian-rebel-vessel-as-colombia-condemns-trumps-accusations-against-petro'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth: He announced U.S. forces hit a vessel linked to a Colombian leftist rebel group and reported three deaths. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/strikes-seventh-alleged-drug-boat-killing-3-hegseth/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>Sen. Lindsey Graham: He said after speaking with the President that tariff rates would be announced Monday. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/international/2025-10-20/trump-threatens-colombias-key-trade-and-security-alliance.html'>El País (English)</a>)</li><li>President Gustavo Petro: He accused the U.S. of murder over a previous strike in which a Colombian fisherman died. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/19/world/americas/trump-colombia-petro-aid.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251020-us-colombia-drug-trade-feud-escalates'>US-Colombia drug trade feud escalates</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/us-says-it-hit-colombian-rebel-vessel-as-trump-calls-petro-%E2%80%98illegal-drug-leader%E2%80%99'>U.S. says it hit Colombian rebel vessel as Trump calls Petro ‘illegal drug leader’</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://english.elpais.com/international/2025-10-20/trump-threatens-colombias-key-trade-and-security-alliance.html'>Trump threatens Colombia’s key trade and security alliance</a> - elpais.com</li